</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FA905881FFF82E2826C7FC22FDB7FE8A" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B2350B0AFFF82E2826C7FC22FDB7FE8A" blockId="11.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E2826C7FC22FEE0FEAE" bold="true" box="[199,328,295,321]" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName id="758A7089FFF82E282435FC22FD0BFEAE" authorityName="Alvarado &amp; Palacio" authorityYear="2021" box="[565,675,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Forrestopius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petiolatus">
<emphasis id="80FED718FFF82E282435FC22FD0BFEAE" box="[565,675,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">petiolatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the elongate first metasomal segment that distinguishes this species from all other in the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
